37562>>>>>    
37562>>>>>    Function IsLoggedIn Returns Boolean
37564>>>>>        String sLoginName
37564>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession bLoggedIn
37564>>>>>        
37564>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37565>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37567>>>>>            Forward Get IsLoggedIn to bLoggedIn
37569>>>>>            Function_Return bLoggedIn
37570>>>>>        End
37570>>>>>>
37570>>>>>        
37570>>>>>        Get psLoginName to sLoginName
37571>>>>>        
37571>>>>>        Function_Return (sLoginName <> "")
37572>>>>>    End_Function
37573>>>>>    
37573>>>>>    
37573>>>>>    //
37573>>>>>    // This procedure is called when validating a session and after logging in. Its purpose is to 
37573>>>>>    // update properties based on the session and user data. Augment this function to update 
37573>>>>>    // properties based on the session / user table. Note that WebAppUser and WebAppSession contain
37573>>>>>    // the right records when this procedure is called.
37573>>>>>    //
37573>>>>>    // Params:
37573>>>>>    //      bClear   True if the procedure is called before session validation to clear properties.
37573>>>>>    //
37573>>>>>    Procedure UpdateSessionProperties Boolean bClear
37575>>>>>        Handle hoUserDD
37575>>>>>        
37575>>>>>        Get phoUserDD to hoUserDD
37576>>>>>        
37576>>>>>        //  Update user properties
37576>>>>>        If (not(bClear) and HasRecord(hoUserDD)) Begin
37578>>>>>            Set psUsername to (Trim(WebAppUser.FullName))
37579>>>>>            Set psLoginName to (Trim(WebAppUser.LoginName))
37580>>>>>            Set piUserRights to WebAppUser.Rights
37581>>>>>            
37581>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesSet 
37582>>>>>        End
37582>>>>>>
37582>>>>>        Else Begin
37583>>>>>            Set psUsername to ""
37584>>>>>            Set psLoginName to ""
37585>>>>>            Set piUserRights to 0
37586>>>>>            
37586>>>>>            Send OnSessionPropertiesClear
37587>>>>>        End
37587>>>>>>
37587>>>>>    End_Procedure
37588>>>>>    
37588>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesSet
37590>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37590>>>>>    End_Procedure
37591>>>>>    
37591>>>>>    Procedure OnSessionPropertiesClear
37593>>>>>        //  Empty event stub
37593>>>>>    End_Procedure
37594>>>>>    
37594>>>>>    Procedure EndSession
37596>>>>>        Integer iErr
37596>>>>>        Boolean bLogWebSession
37596>>>>>        Handle hoSessionDD       
37596>>>>>        
37596>>>>>        Get phoSessionDD to hoSessionDD
37597>>>>>        Get pbLogWebSession to bLogWebSession
37598>>>>>        If not bLogWebSession Begin
37600>>>>>            Forward Send EndSession
37602>>>>>            Procedure_Return
37603>>>>>        End
37603>>>>>>
37603>>>>>            
37603>>>>>        //  Check if session exists
37603>>>>>        Send Clear of hoSessionDD
37604>>>>>        Get psSessionKey to WebAppSession.SessionKey
37605>>>>>        
37605>>>>>        Send Find of hoSessionDD EQ Index.1
37606>>>>>        If (Found) Begin
37608>>>>>            Set Field_Changed_Value of hoSessionDD Field WebAppSession.Active to "N"
37609>>>>>            Get Request_Validate of hoSessionDD to iErr
37610>>>>>            If (iErr) Begin
37612>>>>>                // this should not happen. If it does its a programming error
37612>>>>>                Error DFERR_PROGRAM C_$WebAppSessionValidateFailed
37613>>>>>>
37613>>>>>                Procedure_Return
37614>>>>>            End
37614>>>>>>
37614>>>>>            Send Request_Save of hoSessionDD
37615>>>>>        End
37615>>>>>>
37615>>>>>    End_Procedure
37616>>>>>
37616>>>>>End_Class
