39024>>>
39024>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
39024>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
39024>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
39024>>>        Case Begin
39024>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
39026>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
39026>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
39026>>>                Case Break
39027>>>                
39027>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
39030>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
39030>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
39030>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
39030>>>                Case Break
39031>>>                
39031>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
39034>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
39034>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
39034>>>                Case Break
39035>>>                
39035>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
39035>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
39035>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
39035>>>                  
39035>>>        Case End
39035>>>
39035>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
39035>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
39035>>>        Send SetActionButtons
39036>>>
39036>>>        If (HasRecord(Server(Self))) Begin 
39038>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption    ("Equipo:"*equipo.Nombre)
39039>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption equipo.Nombre
39040>>>        End
39040>>>>
39040>>>        Else Begin 
39041>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption     "Nuevo equipo"
39042>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption "Nuevo"
39043>>>        End
39043>>>>
39043>>>    End_Procedure
39044>>>
39044>>>End_Object
