40352>>>
40352>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
40352>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
40352>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
40352>>>        Case Begin
40352>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
40354>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
40354>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
40354>>>                Case Break
40355>>>                
40355>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
40358>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
40358>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
40358>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
40358>>>                Case Break
40359>>>                
40359>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
40362>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
40362>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
40362>>>                Case Break
40363>>>                
40363>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
40363>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
40363>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
40363>>>                  
40363>>>        Case End
40363>>>
40363>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
40363>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
40363>>>        Send SetActionButtons
40364>>>        
